---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import ProjectCta from '../components/ProjectCta.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Gravity Test Work & Mineral Processing Flowsheet Design"
  description="Representative sampling, gravity amenability tests, size-by-size loss analysis and process design before equipment selection."
>
  <header class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Testing & Process Design' }]} />
      <span class="eyebrow">Evidence before equipment</span>
      <h1>Testing & Process Design</h1>
      <p>
        Our stable in-house capability focuses on gravity amenability and process-direction testing.
        Additional flotation or leaching work is coordinated when the ore requires it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-shell">
      <article class="prose">
        <h2>Representative samples come first</h2>
        <p>
          A precise laboratory result from a biased sample is still misleading. Sampling should
          represent the ore types, size ranges and variability that the future plant will receive.
          We review the sampling context before interpreting a test result.
        </p>
        <h2>Gravity amenability program</h2>
        <p>
          The exact program depends on the mineral, but it can include feed preparation, size
          distribution, staged gravity separation, concentrate cleaning and size-by-size tailings
          checks. The objective is to learn where value reports and what preparation the separation
          requires.
        </p>
        <h2>From test result to flowsheet</h2>
        <p>
          A laboratory machine does not become a plant by increasing its dimensions. Plant design
          adds feed variability, mass flow, water balance, circulating load, sampling points,
          dewatering, tailings and operator control.
        </p>
        <blockquote>
          Initial project assessment is free. Detailed testing, calculations, drawings and equipment
          documentation are scoped according to the work required and may be credited against a
          complete equipment order.
        </blockquote>
      </article>
      <aside class="sidebar">
        <span class="eyebrow">Sample information</span>
        <h2>Before shipping ore</h2>
        <p>
          Contact us first to agree sample mass, particle size, packaging, customs description and
          the questions the test must answer.
        </p>
        <a class="button" href="/assess-my-project/">Plan the test program</a>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
  <ProjectCta title="Let the ore answer the first design question." />
</BaseLayout>
